<?php return '{"menuTree":[{"navigationMenuItem":{"navigationMenuItems":[],"_isDisplayed":true,"_isChildVisible":false,"_data":{"id":187,"contextId":9,"type":"NMI_TYPE_CURRENT","titleLocaleKey":"navigation.current"},"_hasLoadableAdapters":false,"_metadataExtractionAdapters":[],"_extractionAdaptersLoaded":false,"_metadataInjectionAdapters":[],"_injectionAdaptersLoaded":false},"children":[],"_data":{"id":1058,"menuId":22,"menuItemId":187,"parentId":0,"seq":0},"_hasLoadableAdapters":false,"_metadataExtractionAdapters":[],"_extractionAdaptersLoaded":false,"_metadataInjectionAdapters":[],"_injectionAdaptersLoaded":false},{"navigationMenuItem":{"navigationMenuItems":[],"_isDisplayed":true,"_isChildVisible":false,"_data":{"id":191,"contextId":9,"type":"NMI_TYPE_ABOUT","titleLocaleKey":"about.aboutContext"},"_hasLoadableAdapters":false,"_metadataExtractionAdapters":[],"_extractionAdaptersLoaded":false,"_metadataInjectionAdapters":[],"_injectionAdaptersLoaded":false},"children":[],"_data":{"id":1059,"menuId":22,"menuItemId":191,"parentId":0,"seq":1},"_hasLoadableAdapters":false,"_metadataExtractionAdapters":[],"_extractionAdaptersLoaded":false,"_metadataInjectionAdapters":[],"_injectionAdaptersLoaded":false},{"navigationMenuItem":{"navigationMenuItems":[],"_isDisplayed":true,"_isChildVisible":false,"_data":{"id":190,"contextId":9,"type":"NMI_TYPE_ABOUT","titleLocaleKey":"navigation.about"},"_hasLoadableAdapters":false,"_metadataExtractionAdapters":[],"_extractionAdaptersLoaded":false,"_metadataInjectionAdapters":[],"_injectionAdaptersLoaded":false},"children":[{"navigationMenuItem":{"navigationMenuItems":[],"_isDisplayed":true,"_isChildVisible":false,"_data":{"id":296,"contextId":9,"type":"NMI_TYPE_CUSTOM","path":"history","content":{"en_US":"<p>Today in an increasingly industrialized and multifaceted world, it is essential that the educational community at a higher level, organizations, and networks in general, focus their interest on scientific research with the help of the necessary tools for designing research topics of high level.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Under those mentioned above, the idea of creating an Open Access International Multidisciplinary Journal was born as part of the guidelines of the authorities of the University of Guayaquil (UG), led by the Principal, Francisco Mor\\u00e1n Pe\\u00f1a, Ph.D., and Sof\\u00eda Lovato, Ph.D., as Academic Vice Dean. The inflection point started with the Dean of Research, Postgraduate, and Internationalization, who oversees the process for the creation and reactivation of scientific and academic journals of the University of Guayaquil, together with the Coordination of Research and Knowledge Management, and the General Editor of Journals of the University of Guayaquil, Miguel Botto, Ph.D.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>In March 2022, the Faculty of Industrial Engineering assigned Eng. Yomar Gonz\\u00e1lez, Ph.D. as the Editor of the journal EASI: Engineering and Applied Sciences in Industry, beginning an educational adventure by creating the scope and Editorial Committee of the journal \'online\' version, together with a group of professors from the same Faculty, focused on gathering contributions in areas related to the interoperability of the industry and its relationship with society.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The project has been actively supported by the Dean of the Faculty of Industrial Engineering, Jimmy Hurtado Paspuel, M. Sc., and the faculty work team, who continue supporting the hard work of the Executive Editorial Committee of the journal. The biannual EASI journal finally meets the goal for 2022, publishing two issues with the outstanding participation of national and international researchers.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;In this way, EASI continues growing with the vision of becoming a scientific benchmark in the technology applied to industry, including aspects of the relationship with society. The mission currently aims to index the journal in the leading general indices and ensure publication quality. The goal is to position the Faculty in a high ranking at a scientific level, motivating the target audience to participate in topics of research that enhance the curriculum of engineering careers and the research trends at the postgraduate level of the University of Guayaquil.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>EASI was created to disseminate outstanding contributions, including aspects of industry 4.0 and 5.0 and their application on topics such as sustainability, circular economy, logistics, global value chains, and lean techniques, among others, always seeking new solutions for the industry and society.<\\/p>","es_ES":"<p>En un mundo cada vez m\\u00e1s industrializado y complejo como el de hoy, es imperante que la comunidad educativa a nivel superior, organizaciones y redes en general, centren su inter\\u00e9s en la investigaci\\u00f3n cient\\u00edfica con la ayuda de herramientas necesarias para la construcci\\u00f3n de temas investigativos de alto nivel.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>En virtud de lo antes descrito, naci\\u00f3 la idea de crear la revista EASI (Escenario Multidisciplinario Internacional de Acceso Abierto), como parte de las directrices de las autoridades de la Universidad de Guayaquil (UG) lideradas por el Rector, Francisco Mor\\u00e1n Pe\\u00f1a, Ph.D., y Sof\\u00eda Lovato, Ph.D., en calidad de Vicerrectora Acad\\u00e9mica. A partir de ese momento, el Decanato de Investigaci\\u00f3n, Posgrado e Internacionalizaci\\u00f3n es el encargado de llevar el proceso para la creaci\\u00f3n y reactivaci\\u00f3n de revistas cient\\u00edficas y acad\\u00e9micas de la Universidad de Guayaquil, junto con la Coordinaci\\u00f3n de Investigaci\\u00f3n y Gesti\\u00f3n del Conocimiento, y el Editor General de Revistas de la Universidad de Guayaquil, Ing. Miguel Botto, Ph.D.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>En marzo 2022, La Facultad de Ingenier\\u00eda Industrial de la UG designa al Ing. Yomar Gonz\\u00e1lez, Ph.D. como Editor de la Revista de la Facultad; comenzando as\\u00ed una aventura acad\\u00e9mica, al estructurar el objetivo y Comit\\u00e9 Editorial de la versi\\u00f3n \\u2018en l\\u00ednea\\u2019 de la revista EASI: Ingenier\\u00eda y Ciencias Aplicadas en la Industria, en conjunto con un grupo de docentes de la misma Facultad, con el claro prop\\u00f3sito de reunir contribuciones en \\u00e1reas relacionadas con la interoperabilidad de la industria y su relaci\\u00f3n con la sociedad.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>El proyecto ha sido apoyado activamente a trav\\u00e9s de la gesti\\u00f3n liderada por el Decano de la Facultad de Ingenier\\u00eda Industrial, Ing. Jimmy Hurtado Paspuel, M. Sc., y su equipo de trabajo, quienes contin\\u00faan apoyando la ardua labor del comit\\u00e9 Editorial Ejecutivo de la Revista. Es as\\u00ed como la revista bianual EASI cumple su meta para el a\\u00f1o 2022, publicando dos ediciones con la destacada participaci\\u00f3n de investigadores nacionales e internacionales.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>De esta manera EASI contin\\u00faa creciendo con la visi\\u00f3n de convertirse en un referente cient\\u00edfico en la materia de tecnolog\\u00eda aplicada a la industria incluyendo aspectos de su estrecha vinculaci\\u00f3n con la sociedad.&nbsp;Actualmente, la misi\\u00f3n apunta hacia la indexaci\\u00f3n de la revista en los principales \\u00edndices generales y hacia el aseguramiento de la calidad de publicaci\\u00f3n, con el fin de posicionar a la Facultad en un alto ranking a nivel cient\\u00edfico, motivando al p\\u00fablico objetivo a participar en temas de investigaci\\u00f3n que potencien el curr\\u00edculo de las carreras de ingenier\\u00eda, y de las l\\u00edneas de investigaci\\u00f3n a nivel de postgrado de la Universidad de Guayaquil.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>EASI fue concebida para difundir contribuciones de impacto, que incluyan aspectos de la cuarta y quinta revoluci\\u00f3n industrial, y su aplicaci\\u00f3n en temas tales como, sostenibilidad, econom\\u00eda circular, log\\u00edstica, las cadenas globales de valor, t\\u00e9cnicas lean, entre otros; siempre en busca de soluciones tecnol\\u00f3gicas y vers\\u00e1tiles para la gesti\\u00f3n de procesos y para la sociedad en general.&nbsp;<\\/p>"},"remoteUrl":{"en_US":"","es_ES":""},"title":{"en_US":"History","es_ES":"Historia"}},"_hasLoadableAdapters":false,"_metadataExtractionAdapters":[],"_extractionAdaptersLoaded":false,"_metadataInjectionAdapters":[],"_injectionAdaptersLoaded":false},"children":[],"_data":{"id":1061,"menuId":22,"menuItemId":296,"parentId":190,"seq":3},"_hasLoadableAdapters":false,"_metadataExtractionAdapters":[],"_extractionAdaptersLoaded":false,"_metadataInjectionAdapters":[],"_injectionAdaptersLoaded":false},{"navigationMenuItem":{"navigationMenuItems":[],"_isDisplayed":true,"_isChildVisible":false,"_data":{"id":192,"contextId":9,"type":"NMI_TYPE_SUBMISSIONS","titleLocaleKey":"about.submissions"},"_hasLoadableAdapters":false,"_metadataExtractionAdapters":[],"_extractionAdaptersLoaded":false,"_metadataInjectionAdapters":[],"_injectionAdaptersLoaded":false},"children":[],"_data":{"id":1062,"menuId":22,"menuItemId":192,"parentId":190,"seq":4},"_hasLoadableAdapters":false,"_metadataExtractionAdapters":[],"_extractionAdaptersLoaded":false,"_metadataInjectionAdapters":[],"_injectionAdaptersLoaded":false},{"navigationMenuItem":{"navigationMenuItems":[],"_isDisplayed":true,"_isChildVisible":false,"_data":{"id":193,"contextId":9,"type":"NMI_TYPE_EDITORIAL_TEAM","titleLocaleKey":"about.editorialTeam"},"_hasLoadableAdapters":false,"_metadataExtractionAdapters":[],"_extractionAdaptersLoaded":false,"_metadataInjectionAdapters":[],"_injectionAdaptersLoaded":false},"children":[],"_data":{"id":1063,"menuId":22,"menuItemId":193,"parentId":190,"seq":5},"_hasLoadableAdapters":false,"_metadataExtractionAdapters":[],"_extractionAdaptersLoaded":false,"_metadataInjectionAdapters":[],"_injectionAdaptersLoaded":false},{"navigationMenuItem":{"navigationMenuItems":[],"_isDisplayed":true,"_isChildVisible":false,"_data":{"id":194,"contextId":9,"type":"NMI_TYPE_PRIVACY","titleLocaleKey":"manager.setup.privacyStatement"},"_hasLoadableAdapters":false,"_metadataExtractionAdapters":[],"_extractionAdaptersLoaded":false,"_metadataInjectionAdapters":[],"_injectionAdaptersLoaded":false},"children":[],"_data":{"id":1064,"menuId":22,"menuItemId":194,"parentId":190,"seq":6},"_hasLoadableAdapters":false,"_metadataExtractionAdapters":[],"_extractionAdaptersLoaded":false,"_metadataInjectionAdapters":[],"_injectionAdaptersLoaded":false},{"navigationMenuItem":{"navigationMenuItems":[],"_isDisplayed":true,"_isChildVisible":false,"_data":{"id":293,"contextId":9,"type":"NMI_TYPE_CUSTOM","path":"similarity","content":{"en_US":"<p>Similarity Reports provide a summary of matching or highly similar text found in a submitted paper. Only text containing more than 20 matching words will be considered as potential plagiarism, and the score percentage of the manuscript shouldn\\u2019t exceed 10%.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The&nbsp;rating&nbsp;provided by <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.turnitin.com\\/divisions\\/research-publication\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noopener\\">Turnitin<\\/a> is a guide for Editorial Committee to decide if the text within the manuscript is troublesome. In that case, the authors will be reached to clarify the situation. If similarities persist, the manuscript will be rejected immediately.<\\/p>","es_ES":"<p>Los Informes de similitud proporcionan un resumen de texto coincidente o muy similar encontrado en un trabajo enviado. Solo el texto que contenga m\\u00e1s de 20 palabras coincidentes se considerar\\u00e1 plagio potencial, y el porcentaje de puntuaci\\u00f3n del manuscrito no debe exceder el 10 %.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>La calificaci\\u00f3n proporcionada por <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.turnitin.com\\/es\\/division\\/investigacion-publicacion-academica\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noopener\\">Turnitin<\\/a> es una gu\\u00eda para que el Comit\\u00e9 Editorial decida si el texto del manuscrito no re\\u00fane el est\\u00e1ndar necesario. En ese caso, se contactar\\u00e1 a los autores para aclarar la situaci\\u00f3n. Si persisten las similitudes, el manuscrito ser\\u00e1 rechazado de inmediato.<\\/p>"},"remoteUrl":{"en_US":"","es_ES":""},"title":{"en_US":"Similarity policy","es_ES":"Pol\\u00edtica de similitud de contenido"}},"_hasLoadableAdapters":false,"_metadataExtractionAdapters":[],"_extractionAdaptersLoaded":false,"_metadataInjectionAdapters":[],"_injectionAdaptersLoaded":false},"children":[],"_data":{"id":1065,"menuId":22,"menuItemId":293,"parentId":190,"seq":7},"_hasLoadableAdapters":false,"_metadataExtractionAdapters":[],"_extractionAdaptersLoaded":false,"_metadataInjectionAdapters":[],"_injectionAdaptersLoaded":false},{"navigationMenuItem":{"navigationMenuItems":[],"_isDisplayed":true,"_isChildVisible":false,"_data":{"id":253,"contextId":9,"type":"NMI_TYPE_CUSTOM","path":"preservation","content":{"en_US":"<p>EASI use <span class=\\"Y2IQFc\\" lang=\\"es\\"><a href=\\"https:\\/\\/archive.org\\/\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noopener\\">archive.org<\\/a>&nbsp; to <\\/span>build a digital library of the journal web site in digital form. The system provides free access to researchers and the general public. Users also have access to archived copies of the same document, by using <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/archive.org\\/web\\/\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noopener\\">Wayback Machine<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><span class=\\"Y2IQFc\\" lang=\\"es\\">OJS also provides the plug-in <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/docs.pkp.sfu.ca\\/pkp-pn\\/en\\/\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noopener\\">PKP PN<\\/a>&nbsp;to ensure that journal content can be preserved for long-term access.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><span class=\\"Y2IQFc\\" lang=\\"es\\">Besides, published articles are versions of PDF\\/A and XML files.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><iframe src=\\"https:\\/\\/archive.org\\/embed\\/revistas.ug.edu.ecindex.phpeasiissueview182\\" width=\\"560\\" height=\\"384\\" frameborder=\\"0\\" allowfullscreen=\\"\\"><\\/iframe><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><iframe src=\\"https:\\/\\/archive.org\\/embed\\/easi-vol-01-n-02-mejoramiento-del-proceso-de-gestion-artes-graficas\\" width=\\"560\\" height=\\"384\\" frameborder=\\"0\\" allowfullscreen=\\"\\"><\\/iframe><\\/p>","es_ES":"<p><span class=\\"Y2IQFc\\" lang=\\"es\\">Mediante la librer\\u00eda <a href=\\"https:\\/\\/archive.org\\/\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noopener\\">archive.org<\\/a> de libre acceso a los investigadores, se almacenan los contenidos publicados en el sitio de la revista. Incluso, los usuarios pueden atener acceso a las versiones anteriores de un mismo documento mediante la herramienta <\\/span><a href=\\"https:\\/\\/archive.org\\/web\\/\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noopener\\">Wayback Machine<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><span class=\\"Y2IQFc\\" lang=\\"es\\">Se trata de una macro biblioteca digital donde podemos preservar todas las versiones y modificaciones de la informaci\\u00f3n compartida en nuestar p\\u00e1gina web.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><span class=\\"Y2IQFc\\" lang=\\"es\\">El programa complementario&nbsp;<a href=\\"https:\\/\\/docs.pkp.sfu.ca\\/pkp-pn\\/en\\/\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noopener\\">PKP-PN<\\/a>&nbsp;(Preservation Network) en OJS, permite la preservaci\\u00f3n del material publicado y sus sucesivas modificaciones<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><span class=\\"Y2IQFc\\" lang=\\"es\\">Adem\\u00e1s, los art\\u00edculos publicados son versiones de archivos PDF\\/A y XML<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<dl class=\\"metadata-definition\\">\\r\\n<dt><\\/dt>\\r\\n<dt><\\/dt>\\r\\n<\\/dl>\\r\\n<p><iframe src=\\"https:\\/\\/archive.org\\/embed\\/revistas.ug.edu.ecindex.phpeasiissueview182\\" width=\\"560\\" height=\\"384\\" frameborder=\\"0\\" allowfullscreen=\\"\\"><\\/iframe><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><iframe src=\\"https:\\/\\/archive.org\\/embed\\/easi-vol-01-n-02-mejoramiento-del-proceso-de-gestion-artes-graficas\\" width=\\"560\\" height=\\"384\\" frameborder=\\"0\\" allowfullscreen=\\"\\"><\\/iframe><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>"},"remoteUrl":{"en_US":"","es_ES":""},"title":{"en_US":"Preservation Network","es_ES":"Pol\\u00edtica de preservaci\\u00f3n de la informaci\\u00f3n"}},"_hasLoadableAdapters":false,"_metadataExtractionAdapters":[],"_extractionAdaptersLoaded":false,"_metadataInjectionAdapters":[],"_injectionAdaptersLoaded":false},"children":[],"_data":{"id":1066,"menuId":22,"menuItemId":253,"parentId":190,"seq":8},"_hasLoadableAdapters":false,"_metadataExtractionAdapters":[],"_extractionAdaptersLoaded":false,"_metadataInjectionAdapters":[],"_injectionAdaptersLoaded":false}],"_data":{"id":1060,"menuId":22,"menuItemId":190,"parentId":0,"seq":2},"_hasLoadableAdapters":false,"_metadataExtractionAdapters":[],"_extractionAdaptersLoaded":false,"_metadataInjectionAdapters":[],"_injectionAdaptersLoaded":false},{"navigationMenuItem":{"navigationMenuItems":[],"_isDisplayed":true,"_isChildVisible":false,"_data":{"id":188,"contextId":9,"type":"NMI_TYPE_ARCHIVES","titleLocaleKey":"navigation.archives"},"_hasLoadableAdapters":false,"_metadataExtractionAdapters":[],"_extractionAdaptersLoaded":false,"_metadataInjectionAdapters":[],"_injectionAdaptersLoaded":false},"children":[],"_data":{"id":1067,"menuId":22,"menuItemId":188,"parentId":0,"seq":9},"_hasLoadableAdapters":false,"_metadataExtractionAdapters":[],"_extractionAdaptersLoaded":false,"_metadataInjectionAdapters":[],"_injectionAdaptersLoaded":false},{"navigationMenuItem":{"navigationMenuItems":[],"_isDisplayed":true,"_isChildVisible":false,"_data":{"id":189,"contextId":9,"type":"NMI_TYPE_ANNOUNCEMENTS","titleLocaleKey":"manager.announcements"},"_hasLoadableAdapters":false,"_metadataExtractionAdapters":[],"_extractionAdaptersLoaded":false,"_metadataInjectionAdapters":[],"_injectionAdaptersLoaded":false},"children":[],"_data":{"id":1068,"menuId":22,"menuItemId":189,"parentId":0,"seq":10},"_hasLoadableAdapters":false,"_metadataExtractionAdapters":[],"_extractionAdaptersLoaded":false,"_metadataInjectionAdapters":[],"_injectionAdaptersLoaded":false},{"navigationMenuItem":{"navigationM